{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775892475979,"sessionID":"ses_284909cb8ffeOsd4or1kukodLL","part":{"id":"prt_d7b70b048001z7Yx298YP4BbQx","messageID":"msg_d7b70a38e0011RqM8cF1lXKcun","sessionID":"ses_284909cb8ffeOsd4or1kukodLL","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892534137,"sessionID":"ses_284909cb8ffeOsd4or1kukodLL","part":{"id":"prt_d7b70d117001KxWn6IKSJExLtz","messageID":"msg_d7b70a38e0011RqM8cF1lXKcun","sessionID":"ses_284909cb8ffeOsd4or1kukodLL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_9ebb052a7ced450a9226e85d","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: Python SDK/CLI Tests (AR-040)\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python/tests`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine acceptance scenarios for the AgentCube Python SDK test suite, identifying gaps between the existing tests (`sdk-python/tests/`) and the specification (`specs/python-sdk/spec.md`).\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — data plane init failure recovery\n\nThe system SHALL handle `_init_data_plane()` failures gracefully after a session has been created.\n\n### Scenario: Data plane init failure cleans up session\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is initialized without a `session_id`\n- **AND** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session` returns a valid session ID\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning\n- **AND** call `delete_session(session_id)` on the control plane client\n- **AND** set `self.session_id` to `None`\n- **AND** re-raise the original exception\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — execute_command timeout buffer\n\nThe data plane `execute_command` SHALL add a 2.0-second buffer to the read timeout to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124.\n\n### Scenario: Timeout buffer applied to execute_command\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command(command, timeout=30)`\n- **WHEN** the HTTP request is constructed\n- **THEN** the request timeout tuple SHALL be `(connect_timeout, 32.0)` (i.e., `timeout + 2.0`)\n\n### Scenario: Timeout buffer with default timeout\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n- **WHEN** the HTTP request is constructed\n- **THEN** the effective timeout SHALL default to `self.timeout` (120)\n- **AND** the request read timeout SHALL be `122.0` (i.e., `120 + 2.0`)\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: ControlPlaneClient — SA token file fallback\n\nThe control plane client SHALL resolve the auth token from the Kubernetes service account token file when `auth_token` is not provided.\n\n### Scenario: Auth token read from SA file\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` is not provided to `ControlPlaneClient`\n- **AND** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `read_token_from_file(\"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\")`\n- **AND** if the returned token is non-empty, set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` on the session\n\n### Scenario: SA token file not found\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` is not provided\n- **AND** the SA token file does not exist (returns `\"\"` from `read_token_from_file`)\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** no `Authorization` header SHALL be set on the session\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — run_code Python execution flow\n\nThe `CodeInterpreterClient.run_code` method SHALL delegate to the data plane client, which writes a timestamped `.py` file and executes it.\n\n### Scenario: run_code writes timestamped file then executes\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.run_code(\"python\", \"print('hello')\")`\n- **WHEN** the method runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `write_file` with content containing the code\n- **AND** the remote path SHALL include a `.py` extension\n- **AND** it SHALL call `execute_command` with `python3 <remote_path>`\n\n### Scenario: run_code language aliases\n- **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with `language` = `\"py\"` or `\"python3\"`\n- **WHEN** the method runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL follow the same write-file-then-execute path as `\"python\"`\n\n### Scenario: run_code unsupported language\n- **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with an unsupported language (e.g., `\"javascript\"`)\n- **WHEN** the method runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message containing `\"Unsupported language\"`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient — context manager exception handling\n\nThe context manager SHALL properly clean up resources even when an exception occurs in the block.\n\n### Scenario: Context manager exit with exception\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n- **AND** an exception is raised inside the `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`\n- **AND** the data plane client SHALL be closed\n- **AND** the control plane session SHALL be deleted (if `session_id` was set)\n- **AND** the original exception SHALL propagate\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient — invoke header management\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke` method SHALL set session and content-type headers per-request without polluting the session defaults.\n\n### Scenario: Invoke sets per-request session header\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={...})`\n- **WHEN** the POST request is made\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: test-session`\n- **AND** the request SHALL include header `Content-Type: application/json`\n\n### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple construction\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with `connect_timeout=5.0`, `timeout=120`\n- **AND** `invoke(..., timeout=None)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the timeout parameter SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n\n### Scenario: Invoke with custom timeout\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"s\", payload={}, timeout=60)`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the timeout parameter SHALL be `(5.0, 60)`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient — multipart upload headers\n\nFile uploads via multipart form data SHALL include the session header but NOT set `Content-Type: application/json` on the outer request.\n\n### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`\n- **WHEN** the POST request is made\n- **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n- **AND** the request SHALL use `files={'file': ...}` and `data={'path', 'mode'}` parameters\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient — download file path cleaning\n\nThe download file endpoint SHALL strip leading slashes from the remote path.\n\n### Scenario: Download strips leading slash\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(\"/remote/path\", local_path)`\n- **WHEN** the GET request is constructed\n- **THEN** the endpoint SHALL be `api/files/remote/path` (without leading slash)\n\n### Scenario: Download relative path unchanged\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(\"relative/path\", local_path)`\n- **WHEN** the GET request is constructed\n- **THEN** the endpoint SHALL be `api/files/relative/path`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: ControlPlaneClient — delete_session 404 handling\n\nThe `delete_session` method SHALL treat 404 responses as success (idempotent delete).\n\n### Scenario: Delete session returns 404\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"nonexistent-session\")`\n- **WHEN** the server returns HTTP 404\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n\n### Scenario: Delete session other HTTP error\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session\")`\n- **WHEN** the server returns HTTP 500 or raises `HTTPError`\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error\n- **AND** return `False`\n\n### Scenario: Delete session request exception\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session\")`\n- **WHEN** a `requests.exceptions.RequestException` is raised\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error\n- **AND** return `False`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient — invoke response parsing\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke` method SHALL parse the response JSON and return the parsed result.\n\n### Scenario: Invoke returns parsed JSON\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke({\"key\": \"value\"})`\n- **AND** the data plane returns a response with JSON body `{\"result\": \"success\"}`\n- **WHEN** the method completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"result\": \"success\"}` (parsed dict, not raw response)\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Package exports — public API surface\n\nThe `agentcube` package SHALL export only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in its root `__all__`.\n\n### Scenario: Root __all__ contains only public clients\n- **GIVEN** `import agentcube`\n- **WHEN** `agentcube.__all__` is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL equal `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n\n### Scenario: Clients submodule exports internal clients\n- **GIVEN** `from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient`\n- **WHEN** `agentcube.clients.__all__` is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `\"ControlPlaneClient\"`, `\"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\"`, `\"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"`\n\n---\n\n## Test Coverage Gap Summary\n\n| Spec Requirement | Existing Test File | Gap |\n|---|---|---|\n| Data plane init failure recovery | `test_code_interpreter_client.py` | **Missing** — no test for `_init_data_plane` failure cleanup |\n| Execute command timeout buffer (+2.0s) | `test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **Missing** — timeout buffer logic not tested |\n| SA token file fallback | `test_control_plane.py` | **Partial** — tests explicit token but not SA file path fallback |\n| run_code Python execution flow | `test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **Partial** — tests delegation but not write-file-then-execute flow |\n| Context manager exception handling | `test_code_interpreter_client.py` | **Missing** — no test for exception propagation through `__exit__` |\n| Invoke per-request header management | `test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | **Partial** — tests header setting but not per-request isolation |\n| Multipart upload headers | `test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **Partial** — tests session header but not Content-Type absence |\n| Download path cleaning | `test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **Missing** — no test for leading slash stripping |\n| Delete session 404 idempotency | `test_control_plane.py` | **Covered** — `test_delete_session_not_found` exists |\n| Invoke response parsing | `test_agent_runtime_client.py` | **Covered** — `test_invoke_success` tests JSON parsing |\n| Package exports | No dedicated test file | **Missing** — no test for `__all__` contents |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775892534130,"end":1775892534135}}}}
