{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775892557175,"sessionID":"ses_284909cb8ffeOsd4or1kukodLL","part":{"id":"prt_d7b71ed74001ayLzJHOARTXvUV","messageID":"msg_d7b71e1ee001Lydqt4ld7ivKRj","sessionID":"ses_284909cb8ffeOsd4or1kukodLL","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892646788,"sessionID":"ses_284909cb8ffeOsd4or1kukodLL","part":{"id":"prt_d7b71f2b9001Ydotcr8RzZ1z58","messageID":"msg_d7b71e1ee001Lydqt4ld7ivKRj","sessionID":"ses_284909cb8ffeOsd4or1kukodLL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_10d9781f9d1c43b1a793182b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-040: Python SDK/CLI 测试 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `sdk-python/tests`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec defines the test coverage requirements for the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). Existing tests cover basic initialization, delegation, and happy paths for all client classes. This spec identifies **gaps** between the existing test suite and the specification, and defines acceptance scenarios for the missing coverage.\n\n---\n\n## R-1: CodeInterpreterClient — data plane init failure recovery\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` — `__init__`, `_init_data_plane`\n\n### Requirement: Data plane init failure cleans up session\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is initialized without a `session_id`\n  AND `ControlPlaneClient.create_session` returns a valid session ID\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning\n  AND call `delete_session(session_id)` on the control plane client\n  AND set `self.session_id` to `None`\n  AND re-raise the original exception\n\n---\n\n## R-2: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient — execute_command timeout buffer\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — `execute_command`\n\n### Requirement: Timeout buffer (+2.0s) applied to read timeout\n\n#### Scenario: Explicit timeout gets buffer\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command(command, timeout=30)`\n- **WHEN** the HTTP request is constructed\n- **THEN** the request timeout tuple SHALL be `(connect_timeout, 32.0)` (i.e., `timeout + 2.0`)\n\n#### Scenario: Default timeout gets buffer\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n  AND `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n- **WHEN** the HTTP request is constructed\n- **THEN** the effective timeout SHALL be `120`\n  AND the request read timeout SHALL be `122.0` (i.e., `120 + 2.0`)\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout buffer in PicoD timeout string\n\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=30)`\n- **WHEN** the JSON body is constructed\n- **THEN** the body `timeout` field SHALL be `\"30s\"` (original value, not buffered)\n\n---\n\n## R-3: ControlPlaneClient — SA token file fallback\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` — `__init__`\n\n### Requirement: Auth token resolution from SA file\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token read from SA file\n\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` is not provided to `ControlPlaneClient`\n  AND `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `read_token_from_file(\"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\")`\n  AND if the returned token is non-empty, set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` on the session\n\n#### Scenario: SA token file not found\n\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` is not provided\n  AND the SA token file does not exist (`read_token_from_file` returns `\"\"`)\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** no `Authorization` header SHALL be set on the session\n\n#### Scenario: Explicit auth_token takes priority over SA file\n\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token=\"explicit-token\"` is provided\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `read_token_from_file` SHALL NOT be called\n  AND `Authorization: Bearer explicit-token` SHALL be set on the session\n\n---\n\n## R-4: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient — run_code Python execution flow\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — `run_code`\n\n### Requirement: Python code writes file then executes\n\n#### Scenario: run_code writes timestamped .py file then executes\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.run_code(\"python\", \"print('hello')\")`\n- **WHEN** the method runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `write_file` with content containing the code\n  AND the remote path SHALL end with `.py`\n  AND it SHALL call `execute_command` with `python3 <remote_path>`\n\n#### Scenario: run_code language aliases (py, python3)\n\n- **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with `language` = `\"py\"` or `\"python3\"`\n- **WHEN** the method runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL follow the same write-file-then-execute path as `\"python\"`\n\n#### Scenario: run_code unsupported language\n\n- **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with an unsupported language (e.g., `\"javascript\"`)\n- **WHEN** the method runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message containing `\"Unsupported language\"`\n\n---\n\n## R-5: CodeInterpreterClient — context manager exception handling\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` — `__enter__`, `__exit__`, `stop`\n\n### Requirement: Context manager cleans up on exception\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager exit with exception\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n  AND an exception is raised inside the `with` block\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`\n  AND the data plane client SHALL be closed\n  AND the control plane session SHALL be deleted (if `session_id` was set)\n  AND the original exception SHALL propagate\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager exit without exception\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n  AND no exception occurs in the block\n- **WHEN** the block exits normally\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`\n  AND all resources SHALL be cleaned up\n\n---\n\n## R-6: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient — invoke header management\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` — `invoke`\n\n### Requirement: Per-request header isolation\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke sets session header per request\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={...})`\n- **WHEN** the POST request is made\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: test-session`\n  AND the request SHALL include header `Content-Type: application/json`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple construction\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with `connect_timeout=5.0`, `timeout=120`\n  AND `invoke(..., timeout=None)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the timeout parameter SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with custom timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"s\", payload={}, timeout=60)`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the timeout parameter SHALL be `(5.0, 60)`\n\n---\n\n## R-7: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient — multipart upload headers\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — `upload_file`\n\n### Requirement: Multipart upload includes session header, not JSON Content-Type\n\n#### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`\n- **WHEN** the POST request is made\n- **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n  AND the request SHALL use `files={'file': ...}` and `data={'path', 'mode'}` parameters\n  AND the request SHALL NOT set `Content-Type: application/json`\n\n---\n\n## R-8: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient — download file path cleaning\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — `download_file`\n\n### Requirement: Leading slash stripped from remote path\n\n#### Scenario: Download strips leading slash\n\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(\"/remote/path\", local_path)`\n- **WHEN** the GET request is constructed\n- **THEN** the endpoint SHALL be `api/files/remote/path` (without leading slash)\n\n#### Scenario: Download relative path unchanged\n\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(\"relative/path\", local_path)`\n- **WHEN** the GET request is constructed\n- **THEN** the endpoint SHALL be `api/files/relative/path`\n\n---\n\n## R-9: ControlPlaneClient — delete_session error handling\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` — `delete_session`\n\n### Requirement: 404 treated as success, other errors logged\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session returns 404\n\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"nonexistent-session\")`\n- **WHEN** the server returns HTTP 404\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session other HTTP error\n\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session\")`\n- **WHEN** the server returns HTTP 500 or raises `HTTPError`\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error\n  AND return `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete session request exception\n\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session\")`\n- **WHEN** a `requests.exceptions.RequestException` is raised\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error\n  AND return `False`\n\n---\n\n## R-10: AgentRuntimeClient — invoke response parsing\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` — `invoke`\n\n### Requirement: Invoke returns parsed JSON\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke returns parsed JSON dict\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke({\"key\": \"value\"})`\n  AND the data plane returns a response with JSON body `{\"result\": \"success\"}`\n- **WHEN** the method completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"result\": \"success\"}` (parsed dict, not raw response object)\n\n---\n\n## R-11: Package exports — public API surface\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/__init__.py`, `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n\n### Requirement: Root __all__ contains only public clients\n\n#### Scenario: Root __all__ exports\n\n- **GIVEN** `import agentcube`\n- **WHEN** `agentcube.__all__` is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL equal `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n\n### Requirement: Clients submodule exports internal clients\n\n#### Scenario: Clients __all__ exports\n\n- **GIVEN** `from agentcube import clients`\n- **WHEN** `clients.__all__` is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `\"ControlPlaneClient\"`, `\"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\"`, `\"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"`\n\n---\n\n## R-12: ControlPlaneClient — create_session URL and body\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` — `create_session`\n\n### Requirement: Create session HTTP contract\n\n#### Scenario: POST to correct URL with correct body\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` with `base_url = \"http://wm\"`\n- **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"ns\", ttl=7200, metadata={\"k\": \"v\"})` is called\n- **THEN** the request SHALL be `POST http://wm/v1/code-interpreter`\n  AND the JSON body SHALL be `{\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"ns\", \"ttl\": 7200, \"metadata\": {\"k\": \"v\"}}`\n  AND the response `data[\"sessionId\"]` SHALL be returned\n\n#### Scenario: Default parameters in create_session\n\n- **GIVEN** `create_session()` called with no arguments\n- **WHEN** the request is constructed\n- **THEN** the JSON body SHALL be `{\"name\": \"my-interpreter\", \"namespace\": \"default\", \"ttl\": 3600, \"metadata\": None}`\n\n---\n\n## R-13: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient — write_file base64 encoding\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — `write_file`\n\n### Requirement: File content base64 encoded\n\n#### Scenario: write_file encodes content as base64\n\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(\"hello world\", \"/path/to/file\")`\n- **WHEN** the POST request is constructed\n- **THEN** the JSON body `content` field SHALL be the base64 encoding of `\"hello world\"`\n  AND the body `path` SHALL be `\"/path/to/file\"`\n  AND the body `mode` SHALL be `\"0644\"`\n\n---\n\n## R-14: AgentRuntimeClient — bootstrap session ID failure\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` — `__init__`\n\n### Requirement: Bootstrap failure raises ValueError\n\n#### Scenario: Missing session header on bootstrap\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized without `session_id`\n  AND the GET request to the invocation base URL returns no `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n---\n\n## Test Coverage Gap Summary\n\n| Spec Requirement | Existing Test File | Gap Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| Data plane init failure recovery | `test_code_interpreter_client.py` | **Missing** |\n| Execute command timeout buffer (+2.0s) | `test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **Missing** |\n| SA token file fallback | `test_control_plane.py` | **Missing** |\n| run_code write-file-then-execute flow | `test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **Partial** — mocks delegation only |\n| Context manager exception propagation | `test_code_interpreter_client.py` | **Missing** |\n| Invoke per-request header isolation | `test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | **Partial** |\n| Multipart upload Content-Type absence | `test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **Missing** |\n| Download path leading slash stripping | `test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **Missing** |\n| Delete session 404 idempotency | `test_control_plane.py` | **Covered** |\n| Invoke response parsing | `test_agent_runtime_client.py` | **Covered** |\n| Package __all__ exports | No test file | **Missing** |\n| Create session URL/body contract | `test_control_plane.py` | **Partial** |\n| write_file base64 encoding | `test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **Covered** |\n| Bootstrap session ID missing header | `test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | **Covered** |\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `tests/test_code_interpreter_client.py` | **EXISTING** — extend with init failure, context manager exception tests |\n| `tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **EXISTING** — extend with timeout buffer, multipart headers, download path tests |\n| `tests/test_control_plane.py` | **EXISTING** — extend with SA token fallback tests |\n| `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` | **EXISTING** — extend with invoke response parsing edge cases |\n| `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | **EXISTING** — extend with header isolation tests |\n| `tests/test_package_exports.py` | **NEW** — test `__all__` contents for `agentcube` and `agentcube.clients` |\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `pytest` — test framework (existing)\n- `unittest.mock` — mocking (existing, stdlib)\n- `requests` — HTTP client (existing dependency)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/tests/test_code_interpreter_client.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/tests/test_control_plane.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/tests/test_exceptions.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/sdk-python/tests/test_utils.py":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775892646764,"end":1775892646786}}}}
